Diagnosis.
—The new species of 

Alarcta

can be distinguished from the currently known species of the genus using a combination of characters: the number of ribs (12) on the stridulatory apparatus, the body length (
16–18 mm
), forewing length (
20.5–23.3 mm
), and forewing width (7.0– 
7.8 mm
). All other species differ in the combination of these variables to make distinguishing the new species easy (
Table 1
).
